'''Nintendo''', along with its American branch '''Nintendo of America''', is a [[Star Wars video games|video game]] and entertainment company. Their activities includes the conception and manufacturing of various game consoles,<ref name="About" /> for which various ''[[Star Wars]]'' video games have been released, such as the [[Wikipedia:Nintendo Entertainment System|NES]],<ref name="87 SW">[[Star Wars (1987 video game)|''Star Wars'' (1987)]]</ref> [[Wikipedia:Nintendo Game Boy|Game Boy]],<ref name="91 SW">[[Star Wars (1991 video game)|''Star Wars'' (1991)]]</ref> [[Wikipedia:Super Nintendo Entertainment System|SNES]],<ref name="SSW">''[[Super Star Wars]]''</ref> [[Wikipedia:Nintendo 64|Nintendo 64]],<ref name="SotE">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'']]</ref> [[Wikipedia:Game Boy Color|Game Boy Color]],<ref name="Yoda">''[[Star Wars: Yoda Stories]]''</ref> [[Wikipedia:Game Boy Advance|Game Boy Advance]],<ref name="NDA">''[[Star Wars: The New Droid Army]]''</ref> [[Wikipedia:Nintendo GameCube|GameCube]],<ref name="RS II">''[[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron II: Rogue Leader]]''</ref> [[Wikipedia:Nintendo DS|DS]],<ref name="Lethal">''[[Star Wars: Lethal Alliance]]''</ref> [[Wikipedia:Wii|Wii]],<ref name="TCW LD">''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars: Lightsaber Duels]]''</ref> [[Wikipedia:Nintendo 3DS|3DS]],<ref name="LEGO III">''[[LEGO Star Wars III: The Clone Wars]]''</ref> [[Wikipedia:Wii U|Wii U]],<ref name="LEGO TFA">''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]''</ref> and [[Wikipedia:Nintendo Switch|Switch]],<ref name="LEGO Saga">''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Skywalker Saga]]''</ref>. They also directly published several ''Star Wars'' video games for the Nintendo 64: [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Shadows of the Empire'']],<ref name="SotE" /> [[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron (video game)|''Rogue Squadron'']]<ref name="RS"> [[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron (video game)|''Star Wars: Rogue Squadron'']],</ref> and [[Star Wars: Episode I Racer|Episode I ''Racer'']].<ref name="Racer">[[Star Wars: Episode I Racer|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''Racer'']]</ref>

Additionally, they also published guide articles in their official magazine ''[[Nintendo Power]]'', as well as and several associated [[Wikipedia:Nintendo Player's Guide|''Nintendo Player's Guide'']]s: ''[[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron: The Official Nintendo Player's Guide]]'',<ref name="RS Guide" /> [[Star Wars: Episode I Racer Official Nintendo Player's Guide|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''Racer'' Official Nintendo Player's Guide]],<ref name="Racer Guide">[[Star Wars: Episode I Racer Official Nintendo Player's Guide|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''Racer'' Official Nintendo Player's Guide]]</ref> ''[[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron II: Rogue Leader: The Official Nintendo Player's Guide]]'',<ref name="RS II Guide">''[[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron II: Rogue Leader: The Official Nintendo Player's Guide]]''</ref> and ''[[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron III: Rebel Strike: The Official Nintendo Player's Guide]]''.<ref name="RS III Guide">''[[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron III: Rebel Strike: The Official Nintendo Player's Guide]]''</ref>

